Kosuke Ota ( , ta Ksuke, born July 23, 1987 in Tokyo) is a Japanese football player who plays for FC Tokyo in the J. League. At the end of the 2008 season he signed for Shimizu S-Pulse from Yokohama FC.
He made his full international debut for Japan on January 6, 2010 in a 2011 AFC Asian Cup qualifier against Yemen.

